## Environment variables

{{#hasNeon}}
### Neon (PostgreSQL)

1. Create a free account at [neon.tech](https://neon.tech)
2. Create a new project
3. Copy the connection string from the dashboard

```
DATABASE_URL=postgresql://user:pass@ep-xxx.neon.tech/dbname?sslmode=require
```
{{/hasNeon}}

{{#hasFirestore}}
### Firestore

1. Go to [Firebase Console](https://console.firebase.google.com)
2. Create a project → Firestore Database → Create database
3. Project Settings → Service accounts → Generate new private key
4. Copy values from the downloaded JSON file

```
FIREBASE_PROJECT_ID=your-project-id
FIREBASE_CLIENT_EMAIL=firebase-adminsdk@your-project.iam.gserviceaccount.com
FIREBASE_PRIVATE_KEY="-----BEGIN PRIVATE KEY-----\n...\n-----END PRIVATE KEY-----\n"
```
{{/hasFirestore}}

{{#hasUpstashRedis}}
### Upstash Redis

1. Create a free account at [upstash.com](https://upstash.com)
2. Create a new Redis database
3. Copy REST URL and token from the database details

```
UPSTASH_REDIS_REST_URL=https://xxx.upstash.io
UPSTASH_REDIS_REST_TOKEN=AXxx...
```
{{/hasUpstashRedis}}

{{#hasClerk}}
### Clerk

1. Create a free account at [clerk.com](https://clerk.com)
2. Create a new application
3. Dashboard → API Keys

```
NEXT_PUBLIC_CLERK_PUBLISHABLE_KEY=pk_test_...
CLERK_SECRET_KEY=sk_test_...
```
{{/hasClerk}}

{{#hasFirebaseAuth}}
### Firebase Auth

1. Go to [Firebase Console](https://console.firebase.google.com)
2. Authentication → Get started → enable your sign-in methods
3. Project Settings → Your apps → Add app → Web

```
NEXT_PUBLIC_FIREBASE_API_KEY=AIza...
NEXT_PUBLIC_FIREBASE_AUTH_DOMAIN=your-project.firebaseapp.com
NEXT_PUBLIC_FIREBASE_PROJECT_ID=your-project-id
```
{{/hasFirebaseAuth}}

{{#hasSupabaseAuth}}
### Supabase Auth

1. Create a free project at [supabase.com](https://supabase.com)
2. Project Settings → API

```
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL=https://xxx.supabase.co
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=eyJhbGciOi...
```
{{/hasSupabaseAuth}}

{{#hasR2}}
### Cloudflare R2

1. Cloudflare Dashboard → R2 → Create bucket
2. Manage R2 API Tokens → Create API token (Object Read & Write)
3. Account ID is on the R2 overview page

```
R2_ACCOUNT_ID=abc123
R2_ACCESS_KEY_ID=key123
R2_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY=secret123
R2_BUCKET_NAME=my-bucket
R2_PUBLIC_URL=https://pub-xxx.r2.dev
```
{{/hasR2}}

{{#hasResend}}
### Resend

1. Create a free account at [resend.com](https://resend.com)
2. Add and verify your sending domain (or use the sandbox domain for testing)
3. API Keys → Create API Key

```
RESEND_API_KEY=re_...
RESEND_FROM_EMAIL=noreply@yourdomain.com
```
{{/hasResend}}

{{#hasStripe}}
### Stripe

1. Create an account at [stripe.com](https://stripe.com)
2. Developers → API keys (use test keys for development)
3. Developers → Webhooks → Add endpoint → `https://your-api-url/api/webhooks/stripe`
   - Listen for: `payment_intent.succeeded`, `checkout.session.completed`
4. Reveal the webhook signing secret

```
STRIPE_SECRET_KEY=sk_test_...
NEXT_PUBLIC_STRIPE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY=pk_test_...
STRIPE_WEBHOOK_SECRET=whsec_...
```

**Testing webhooks locally:**
```bash
# Install Stripe CLI: https://stripe.com/docs/stripe-cli
stripe login
stripe listen --forward-to localhost:8080/api/webhooks/stripe
```
{{/hasStripe}}

{{#hasLlmApi}}
### Anthropic API

1. Create an account at [console.anthropic.com](https://console.anthropic.com)
2. API Keys → Create Key

```
ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=sk-ant-...
```
{{/hasLlmApi}}

{{#hasVectorRag}}
### Pinecone

1. Create a free account at [pinecone.io](https://pinecone.io)
2. Create an index (dimension: 1536 for text-embedding-3-small, or 3072 for text-embedding-3-large)
3. API Keys → Create API Key

```
ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=sk-ant-...
PINECONE_API_KEY=pcsk_...
PINECONE_INDEX=my-index
```
{{/hasVectorRag}}

{{#isCloudRun}}
### Google Cloud Run

1. Install gcloud CLI: https://cloud.google.com/sdk/docs/install
2. Run: `gcloud auth login`
3. Create a project at https://console.cloud.google.com
4. Enable APIs: `gcloud services enable run.googleapis.com cloudbuild.googleapis.com`

```
GCP_PROJECT_ID=your-project-id
GCP_REGION=us-central1
```
{{/isCloudRun}}

