## Deploying

### One-command deploy

```bash
npm run deploy
```

{{#isCloudflarePages}}
**First time setup (Cloudflare Pages):**
```bash
npm install -g wrangler
wrangler login
# Create the project first (one time):
wrangler pages project create {{projectName}}
```
{{/isCloudflarePages}}

{{#isVercel}}
**First time setup (Vercel):**
```bash
npm install -g vercel
vercel login
# Link project (one time, from apps/web):
cd apps/web && vercel
```
{{/isVercel}}

{{#isFirebaseHosting}}
**First time setup (Firebase Hosting):**
```bash
npm install -g firebase-tools
firebase login
firebase init hosting   # select your project, set public dir to dist
```
{{/isFirebaseHosting}}

{{#isNetlify}}
**First time setup (Netlify):**
```bash
npm install -g netlify-cli
netlify login
netlify init   # from apps/web
```
{{/isNetlify}}

{{#isCloudRun}}
**Deploy backend (Cloud Run):**
```bash
gcloud auth login
gcloud config set project $GCP_PROJECT_ID
npm run deploy
```
{{/isCloudRun}}

{{#isRender}}
**Deploy backend (Render):**
1. Go to [dashboard.render.com](https://dashboard.render.com)
2. New → Web Service → Connect your GitHub repo
3. Set root directory to `apps/api`
4. Add all environment variables from `.env`
5. Render will auto-deploy on every push to `main`
{{/isRender}}

{{#isFlyio}}
**Deploy backend (Fly.io):**
```bash
# Install: https://fly.io/docs/flyctl/install/
fly auth login
cd apps/api
fly launch    # creates fly.toml, one time
fly deploy    # or just: npm run deploy from root
```
{{/isFlyio}}

### CI/CD (GitHub Actions)

The `.github/workflows/deploy.yml` file deploys automatically on every push to `main`.

Add these secrets to your GitHub repository (Settings → Secrets → Actions):

{{#isCloudflarePages}}
- `CLOUDFLARE_API_TOKEN` — Cloudflare dashboard → My Profile → API Tokens → Create Token (use "Edit Cloudflare Pages" template)
{{/isCloudflarePages}}
{{#isVercel}}
- `VERCEL_TOKEN` — Vercel dashboard → Settings → Tokens
{{/isVercel}}
{{#isFirebaseHosting}}
- `FIREBASE_SERVICE_ACCOUNT` — Firebase console → Project settings → Service accounts → Generate key (paste the entire JSON)
- `FIREBASE_PROJECT_ID` — Your Firebase project ID
{{/isFirebaseHosting}}
{{#isNetlify}}
- `NETLIFY_AUTH_TOKEN` — Netlify dashboard → User Settings → Personal access tokens
- `NETLIFY_SITE_ID` — Netlify dashboard → Site settings → Site ID
{{/isNetlify}}
{{#isCloudRun}}
- `GCP_SA_KEY` — GCP service account JSON key with Cloud Run and Cloud Build permissions
- `GCP_REGION` — e.g. `us-central1`
{{/isCloudRun}}
{{#isFlyio}}
- `FLY_API_TOKEN` — `fly auth token`
{{/isFlyio}}

